com.google.zxing.common.reedsolomon

Class GenericGFPoly

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.zxing.common.reedsolomon.GenericGFPoly

  • final class GenericGFPoly
extends java.lang.Object

    Represents a polynomial whose coefficients are elements of a GF. Instances of this class are immutable.

    Much credit is due to William Rucklidge since portions of this code are an indirect port of his C++ Reed-Solomon implementation.

    Author:
    Sean Owen

    • Constructor Detail

      • GenericGFPoly

        GenericGFPoly(GenericGF field,
             int[] coefficients)
        Parameters:
        field - the GenericGF instance representing the field to use to perform computations
        coefficients - coefficients as ints representing elements of GF(size), arranged from most significant (highest-power term) coefficient to least significant
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if argument is null or empty, or if leading coefficient is 0 and this is not a constant polynomial (that is, it is not the monomial "0")
